index=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Feb 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qzy1707825586891.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qzy1707825586891.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qzy1707825586891.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lty1665702620424\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      \n      Date and Time Constants\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To create date and time constants, each unit of date and time has its own code which can only be used in combination with numeric integer constants.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lty1665702620424__p_d14939e1_d14940e1_d14941e1\">For example, <code class=\"ph codeph\">17n</code> is valid, <code class=\"ph codeph\">$REG$n</code> is not valid, but the expression <code class=\"ph codeph\">$REG$*1n</code> is valid.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lty1665702620424__p_d14942e1_d14943e1_d14944e1\">There are no date and time constant codes for months or years because neither of these contains a fixed number of days; if you need to add or subtract months from a date, use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">addmonths</span> statement. Weeks are not represented here because they are superfluous, that is, a week is always seven days ( <code class=\"ph codeph\">7d</code>).</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"4\" id=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Codes for Date and Time Constants</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__1\">\n Code\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__3\">\n Examples\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__4\">\n Value (fraction of 1 day)\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">d</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__2\">\n Day\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__3\">\n 1d\n <p class=\"p\">3d</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__4\">\n 1\n <p class=\"p\">3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">h</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__2\">\n Hour\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__3\">\n 1h\n <p class=\"p\">2h</p>\n<p class=\"p\">1d6h</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__4\">\n 1/24\n <p class=\"p\">1/12</p>\n<p class=\"p\">1 &amp; 1/4</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__2\">\n Minute\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__3\">\n 1n\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__4\">\n 1/1,440\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">s</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__2\">\n Second\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__3\">\n 1s\n <p class=\"p\">1n2s</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__4\">\n 1/86,400\n <p class=\"p\">62/86,400 or 31/43,200</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">t</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__2\">\n Tick\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__3\">\n 1t\n <p class=\"p\">5t</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lty1665702620424__table_d1532e1_d1533e1_d1534e1__entry__4\">\n 1/8,640,000\n <p class=\"p\">5/8,640,000 or 1/1,728,000</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/exh1665702554603.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>addmonths</a><p>Adds the specified number of months to the date, storing the result of the calculation in $result.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6108860\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6108860\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Date and Time Constants Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Feb 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Date and Time Constants To create date and time constants, each unit of date and time has its own code which can only be used in combination with numeric integer constants. For example, 17n is valid, $REG$n is not valid, but the expression $REG$*1n is valid. There are no date and time constant codes for months or years because neither of these contains a fixed number of days; if you need to add or subtract months from a date, use the addmonths statement. Weeks are not represented here because they are superfluous, that is, a week is always seven days ( 7d ). Table 1. Codes for Date and Time Constants Code Meaning Examples Value (fraction of 1 day) d Day 1d 3d 1 3 h Hour 1h 2h 1d6h 1/24 1/12 1 & 1/4 n Minute 1n 1/1,440 s Second 1s 1n2s 1/86,400 62/86,400 or 31/43,200 t Tick 1t 5t 1/8,640,000 5/8,640,000 or 1/1,728,000 Related Links addmonths Adds the specified number of months to the date, storing the result of the calculation in $result. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}